{
  "texts": [
    "Its radius θ E is known as the Einstein radius.",
    "Because of the aforementioned property of circular mass distributions, the Einstein ring will be the same for any circular distribution of mass within θ E provided the integrated κ equals πθ 2 E -in particular a uniform distribution with κ = 1 inside the disk.",
    "This property lets us define a notional θ E even when a mass distribution is not circular: as the radius of a region whose mean enclosed κ is unity.",
    "The mass M corresponding to a given Einstein radius will be πθ 2 E cr and thus",
    "For a given mass, θ E decreases with distance."
  ]
}